  "prompt": "How can I drag myself out of depression?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help manage depression:\n\n1. Professional Help\n- See a therapist or counselor\n- Consider medication if recommended by a professional\n- Join support groups\n\n2. Lifestyle Changes\n- Exercise regularly\n- Maintain a consistent sleep schedule\n- Eat a balanced, nutritious diet\n- Limit alcohol and avoid drugs\n\n3. Mental Health Techniques\n- Practice mindfulness and meditation\n- Use positive self-talk\n- Set small, achievable goals\n- Challenge negative thoughts\n\n4. Social Support\n- Connect with friends and family\n- Share your feelings\n- Don't isolate yourself\n\n5. Self-Care\n- Engage in activities you enjoy\n- Practice good personal hygiene\n- Spend time in nature\n- Get sunlight and fresh air\n\n6. Stress Management\n- Practice relaxation techniques\n- Learn stress reduction methods\n- Try yoga or deep breathing exercises\n\n7. Routine\n- Create a daily structure\n- Set a consistent schedule\n- Break tasks into smaller steps\n\n8. Additional Support\n- Consider calling a mental health helpline\n- Use mental health apps\n- Read self-help books\n\nRemember, recovery takes time. Be patient and kind to yourself. If you're having severe symptoms or suicidal thoughts, seek immediate professional help.",
